Quote: <i>Pig-face, Pig-faces</i>, and <i>Pig's-face</i>, or <i>Pig's-faces</i>. Names given to an indigenous `ice-plant,' <i>Mesembryanthemum aequilaterale</i>, Haw., <i>N.O. Ficoideae</i>, deriving its generic name from the habit of expanding its flower about noon.[1834]
